headline.main: AFRICAN PUSH IS ON; British Fleet Bombards Halfaya While Troops Sweep Into Libya

lead_paragraph: CAIRO, Egypt, Nov. 19 -- While heavy rain turned the desert dust into a pasty gumbo yesterday, Britain's Eighth Army, under the command of the conqueror of the Italian East Africa, Lieut. Gen. Sir Alan Gordon Cunningham, and led by armored divisions, attacked on a 130-mile front and slogged westward into Libya.
